---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Nearcon 2023 — AES" bodyClass="inner-page">

  <div class="container-fluid event-hero">
    <div class="event-hero-inner">
      <div class="event-hero-left">
        <div class="event-location">Lisbon, Portugal</div>
        <div class="event-title">Nearcon<br />2023</div>
        <div class="event-tagline">
          A successful decentralized event showcasing 5 venues, nearly 2,000 attendees, and 30 sponsors from the Near ecosystem.
        </div>
        <div class="event-hero-photo">
          <div class="event-hero-photo-item" style="background-image: url('/images/work1.png')"></div>
          <div class="event-hero-photo-item" style="background-image: url('/images/work2.png')"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="event-hero-right">
        <div class="event-detail-card">
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">Production</div>
            <p>Our lease on the warehouse started about 10 days before the event. In that time, we made roof repairs and installed all major infrastructure. After that, over 35 partners moved into their custom booths and the team at Europalco built 4 stages including 2 silent discos.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">Registration</div>
            <p>Attendees started arriving an hour early for pre-registration, so we opened early and were ready to go. Our registration carnival was the driest day of the event. Over the next 3 days, weather-related power and internet outages slowed registration but never stopped it — no lines, no problem.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">On-Site</div>
            <p>We've never run an event through a natural disaster, but we made it work. We closed one stage for a few hours on day one but kept everything else right on track. One of the most rewarding experiences of our careers — and a testament to a client who showed full trust in our team in a crisis.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid event-gallery">
    <div class="event-gallery-inner">
      <div class="gallery-grid">
        <div class="gallery-placeholder gallery-large" style="background-image: url('/images/work3.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder" style="background-image: url('/images/work5.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder" style="background-image: url('/images/work7.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder gallery-large" style="background-image: url('/images/work9.png')"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid event-back">
    <div class="event-back-inner">
      <a href="/work" class="cr-btn white ex-padding">← Back to All Events</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
